On 04/17/2018 10:27 AM, Obenchain, Valerie wrote:

Hi developers,

Tomorrow we are bringing a web app online to help with the management of SSH keys. The app will replace the Google Sheet currently used to add keys. Through the web interface you'll be able to add keys and change your email or github username. There is also an option to see what packages you have access to.

Using the app is not a requirement. It's intended to help package authors get setup with keys and access to their package in the Bioconductor git repository. Those of you already set up with keys and access may never need to use it.

Tomorrow, April 18, we'll have downtime from 9-11am EST while we take down the Google Sheet and bring up the app.

Thanks.

Valerie and Nitesh


